Put oven rack in middle position and preheat oven to 500Â°F. Melt butter in a 17- by 12-inch shallow baking pan in oven, about 2 minutes. Spread tortillas, in baking pan, overlapping slightly and turning each over once to coat with butter. Stir together sugar, cinnamon, and a pinch of salt. Sprinkle evenly over tortillas. Bake tortillas until golden and puffed in spots, 4 to 5 minutes.